</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-79_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-80_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regular training</strong> - Keeping skills and knowledge up to date is vital for responding appropriately to safeguarding issues.






</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-82_ pf-text-1"><strong>Multi-agency cooperation </strong>-<strong>&nbsp;</strong>Collaboration between health, social care, and law enforcement agencies ensures comprehensive protection strategies.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-84_ pf-text-1"><strong>Creating safe environments</strong> - Ensuring that all settings where children are present are safe from potential harm.






